  "texts": [
    "In this schematic overview, the central focus is on the exoskeleton user, around whom a comprehensive set of data is gathered from both the robotic system and multimodal patient monitoring.",
    "This influx of information is then directed into two pivotal modules: LC and ID.",
    "The former aims at discerning high-level parameters related to walking, such as step-phase and terrain characteristics, while the latter focuses on identifying the user's intention to initiate walking.",
    "The outputs from these modules converge into the trajectory generation system, a critical component tasked with predicting the joint angles necessary for the exoskeleton to generate a walking pattern customized to the individual's anthropometric dimensions.",
    "Ultimately, the culmination of this predictive information guides the RC module, which takes charge of the actual actuation system."
  ],
